EXPERIMENT 4

Build a React application and configure a fully automated CI/CD pipeline using Git/GitHub, Jenkins, and Docker. Use Jenkins cron jobs to trigger the pipeline automatically and deploy the application on Kubernetes.

==================================================================
CREATE REACT APPLICATION
==================================================================

Create a React project using Vite.

npm create vite@latest react-k8s-app

Select:

Framework : React
Variant : JavaScript

Move to the project folder.

cd react-k8s-app

Install dependencies.

npm install

Run the application.

npm run dev

Open browser.

http://localhost:5173

Build the application.

npm run build

==================================================================
INITIALIZE GIT
==================================================================

git init

git add .

git commit -m "Initial Commit"

Create a GitHub repository named:

react-k8s-app

Connect GitHub repository.

git remote add origin https://github.com/USERNAME/react-k8s-app.git

git branch -M main

git push -u origin main

==================================================================
CREATE DOCKERFILE
==================================================================

Create a file named Dockerfile.

Paste the following code.

FROM node:20

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./

RUN npm install

COPY . .

RUN npm run build

RUN npm install -g serve

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["serve","-s","dist","-l","3000"]

==================================================================
BUILD DOCKER IMAGE
==================================================================

docker build -t react-k8s-app .

Run Docker container.

docker run -d -p 3000:3000 --name react-container react-k8s-app

Open browser.

http://localhost:3000

(Optional)

docker login

docker tag react-k8s-app USERNAME/react-k8s-app

docker push USERNAME/react-k8s-app

==================================================================
CREATE KUBERNETES DEPLOYMENT FILE
==================================================================

Create a file named deployment.yaml

Paste the following code.

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: react-deployment

spec:
  replicas: 2

  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: react-app

  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: react-app

    spec:
      containers:
      - name: react-container
        image: react-k8s-app
        imagePullPolicy: Never
        ports:
        - containerPort: 3000

---

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service

metadata:
  name: react-service

spec:
  selector:
    app: react-app

  ports:
  - port: 3000
    targetPort: 3000

  type: NodePort

==================================================================
CREATE JENKINS PIPELINE
==================================================================

Open Jenkins.

http://localhost:8080

Create New Item.

Name:

React-Kubernetes

Select:

Pipeline

Click OK.

Pipeline Definition:

Pipeline script from SCM

SCM:

Git

Repository URL:

https://github.com/USERNAME/react-k8s-app.git

Branch:

*/main

Script Path:

Jenkinsfile

Enable Build periodically.

Cron Expression:

H/2 * * * *

==================================================================
CREATE JENKINSFILE
==================================================================

Create a file named Jenkinsfile.

Paste the following code.

pipeline {
    agent any

    triggers {
        cron('H/2 * * * *')
    }

    stages {

        stage('Clone Repository') {
            steps {
                checkout scm
            }
        }

        stage('Install Dependencies') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm install'
            }
        }

        stage('Build React Application') {
            steps {
                sh 'npm run build'
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t react-k8s-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy to Kubernetes') {
            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }
}

Save the Jenkinsfile.

Push changes to GitHub.

git add .

git commit -m "Added Jenkins Pipeline"

git push origin main

==================================================================
DEPLOY TO KUBERNETES
==================================================================

Start Minikube.

minikube start

Apply deployment.

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml

Check deployments.

kubectl get deployments

Check pods.

kubectl get pods

Check services.

kubectl get services

Open the application.

minikube service react-service

